  "text": "Drive/Receiver Field Trajectories MPI images are formed by translating the FFR using drive field scanning trajectories and detecting the SPIO signals with a set of receiver coils with varying coil sensitivity profiles [CITATION_1] . Using a drive field along an unit arbitrary trajectory vector u a (t), and a receiver coil with unit coil sensitivity u b (t), as in Eqn. 3, the image produced is a projection of the native tensor image (x) onto the two respective vectors:",
